text: Air Atlanta Europe is an airline from Malta.Malta's Air Atlanta Europe to end B747 passenger ops ==History== The airline was founded on 2002 in United Kingdom. The airline stopped operations in 2008.Air Atlanta Europe buys two B777-200ERs In 2021, Air Atlanta Europe opened again in Malta, to operate Boeing 777 passenger aircrafts. In 2025, the Icelandic airline integrated its first Boeing 777.Air Atlanta opens new chapter with move to 777s ==Fleet== Air Atlanta Europe's fleet consists of 10 aircraft as of February 2025:Air Atlanta Europe Fleet Detail * Boeing 747F * Boeing 777-200ER * Boeing 777-300ER ==References== ==Other websites== * Category:2002 establishments in Europe Category:Airlines of Europe Category:Organizations based in Malta
